result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher B. Trotter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fraud Against Financial Institution (Value Exceeds $500 but does not Exceed $10,000), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.82(1).
  • Fraud Against Financial Institution (Value Exceeds $500 but does not Exceed $10,000) [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.82(1).
  • Fraud Against Financial Institution (Value Exceeds $500 but does not Exceed $10,000) [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.82(1).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).
  • Misappropriate ID Info - Obtain Money [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: All counts are concurrent with each other.

superMiscConds.notes:
One-half of the amount of restitution taken from the bond.  Balance of restitution to be paid to Agent.  
Joint and several.

**11-02-2016 - Restitution amended per the Judge to reflect Christopher's half of the amount of requested restitution.  Christopher's portion of restitution is paid in full.
All costs are paid.  Bond applied.  Any balance of bond to be returned to poster.

If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due, and/or other collection means, such as income assignment will be issued.  The Defendant is to undergo any counseling the agent finds appropriate and must comply with any recommended treatment/assessment/counseling.  Defendant may not withdraw from any ordered program without permission of the agent and/or provider.  The Defendant is to obtain and maintain full time employment.  The Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol or drugs unless prescribed by a physician.  The Defendant is to have no contact with E.H.   The Defendant is subject to random drug/alcohol/UA testing.  The Defendant is to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis.  Extended Supervision may be transferred to Illinois once released from prison.
